.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This bundle is more or less the original configuration bundled with
Dist::Zilla.  More than likely, you'd rather be using
\&\f(CW@Basic\fR or a more complex bundle.  This one
will muck around with your code by adding \f(CW$VERSION\fR declarations and will
mess with you Pod by adding a \f(CW\*(C`=head1 VERSION\*(C'\fR section, but it won't get you a
lot of more useful features like autoversioning, autoprereqs, or Pod::Weaver.
.PP
